<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-2979] FtpComponent: If login fails and disconnect=true another connection is opened.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-2979</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In a route such as below a second connection to the ftp server is opened if the login fails.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;route&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;from uri=&quot;ftp:localhost/inbox/?username=usr&amp;amp;password=pwd&amp;amp;disconnect=true&amp;amp;consumer.delay=60s&amp;amp;maximumReconnectAttempts=0&quot; /&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;to uri=&quot;file:test_data&quot; /&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/route&amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Further description: &lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/FTP-Try-login-once-and-disconnect-if-failure-td1692660.html#a1692660&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/FTP-Try-login-once-and-disconnect-if-failure-td1692660.html#a1692660&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
